In Germany, corruption, in particular bribery and bribery and the acceptance and approval of advantages, is prosecuted under criminal and labour law.
In order to prevent corruption, the Federal Government has issued a directive and recommendations on the prevention of corruption 12 in the Federal Administration.
Furthermore, other anti-corruption requirements have been incorporated into the public procurement rules.
