Calculation methods for estimated order value
In the road sector, existing price databases were insufficient to determine expected order values.
The data were based on just completed construction projects, however, where there was evidence of a lack of efficiency, unnecessary additional performance effort or excessive profits by the contracted firms.
For three sections of a motorway ring, actual prices were about 37 percent below the estimated order values determined by the database.
