Summary findings
Both countries broadly agree on documentation and reporting requirements and implement EU requirements.
This will in principle ensure the transparency of procurement procedures, including procurement.
The rules to be applied in the Czech Republic for notification go a little further than those in Germany.
The weaknesses identified in documentation and notices substantially limited the or corruption-preventive effect of these instruments in the respective procurement procedures.
